When people ask me if I ever get lonely being single the answer is always the same.

"How can I be lonely when I have an Indie?"

It just amazes me how much love and company one dog can give. Indie is never far from my side and her new favorite thing is when I pretend to put makeup on her when I'm getting ready. I laugh every time I pretend to blend her blush.

Earlier this year when I lost Liberty, I thought to myself "I'll never have another dog who loved that much again." I was wrong.

Liberty would be proud of Indie for doing such a good job of loving her Mom.

You might have seen the Reel that I posted and I have to explain! I've been getting tattooed for 28 years and I often wonder what I would look like if I didn't have my tattoos. So I grabbed some coverup (Dermablend) and started painting. I absolutely did not like it and I absolutely will not be doing that again. I love my tattoos but Im also glad I tried it so now when people say "I'm going to regret my tattoos when I'm older" I know for sure that they are 100% wrong!!!
